Form/panel/FormPanel.js.description:
Form Panel is a ready to use form builder inherited for Pydio's legacy parameters formats ('standard form').
It is very versatile and can basically take a set of parameters defined in the XML manifests (or defined manually
in JS) and display them as a user form.
It is a controlled component: it takes a {values} object and triggers back an onChange() function.

See also Manager class to get some utilitary functions to parse parameters and extract values for the form.

values.description: Object containing values for the parameters

onParameterChange.description: Trigger unitary function when one form input changes.

onChange.description: Send all form values onchange, including eventually the removed ones (for dynamic panels)

onValidStatusChange.description:
Triggered when the form globabally switches between valid and invalid state
Triggered once at form construction

disabled.description: Disable the whole form at once

header.description: Add an additional header component (added inside first subpanel)

footer.description: Add an additional footer component (added inside last subpanel)

additionalPanes.description: Add other arbitrary panels, either at the top or the bottom

tabs.description:
An array of tabs containing groupNames. Groups will be splitted
accross those tabs
